n class="Button__labelItem">More details</span></button></div></div></div><hr class="Divider" role="presentation"/><div class="AuthorPreview"><div class="AuthorPreview__profile"><div class="AuthorPreview__avatar"><a class="Avatar Avatar--large" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6887314.Noelle_Stevenson" as="div"><img data-testid="image" class="Avatar__image" alt="Noelle Stevenson" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1643506938i/6887314._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg"/></a></div><div class="AuthorPreview__info"><h3 class="Text H3"><a class="ContributorLink" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6887314.Noelle_Stevenson"><span class="ContributorLink__name" data-testid="name">Noelle Stevenson</span></a></h3><div class="AuthorPreview__meta"><span class="Text Text__body3 Text__subdued">39<!-- --> <!-- -->books<span class="u-dot-before">4,243<!-- --> <!-- -->followers</span></span></div></div></div><div class="TruncatedText"><div class="TruncatedText__text TruncatedText__text--3" data-testid="contentContainer"><div><span class="Formatted">Noelle Stevenson (he/she/they) is a comic artist and freelance illustrator residing in Los Angeles, California. He published the young adult graphic novel NIMONA in 2015, which is also serialized online. Noelle has been nominated for a Harvey Award, and was awarded the Slate Cartoonist Studio Prize for Best Webcomic in 2012. Noelle is a graduate of the Maryland Institute College of Art and has done published work for BOOM! Studios, Random House, MacMillan Press, and What Pumpkin Studios, among others. They are the co-writer of LUMBERJANES, a comic series from BOOM! Box, and has done writing work for Frederator's BRAVEST WARRIORS as well.</span></div></div></div></div><hr class="Divider" role="presentation"/><div class="NativeAdWrapper"> <div class="Ad Ad__nativeAd Ad--showDividers" id="div-gpt-goodr-book-2"></div> </div></div><div class="BookPage__relatedTopContent"><div><div class="Loa